5:
It's certainly exciting fighting monsters 
on their home turf. They're more active 
than they are at the arena.
9:
So this is where the arena's been 
finding all those monsters...
11:
Why did you want to come down here? 
To compare the Kaleidoscope 
monsters to the arena's?
15:
Yep. I needed to challenge myself, to 
find fresh opponents.
18:
Everyone tells me I fight with elegance. 
But that's because I specialize in battle 
choreography—stage fighting, as it 
were.
19:
It's flashy, but it wouldn't hold up in 
a real fight. I'm a "fighter" in name 
only. Laughable, really.
22:
It would break my heart if 
I disappointed my fans, though. 
I want to show them what I'm truly 
capable of!
25:
What do you think of my swordplay, 
Alk?
30: I guess it is pretty flashy.
34:
But I don't think that's a bad thing. 
You've got poise—REAL poise.
37:
Even when your back's against the 
wall, you never lose your edge. 
I think that's amazing.
40:
You may not believe it yourself, but 
you ARE amazing, Eclair.
44: Alk... I like your swordplay too.
48:
Really? That's great to hear coming 
from you!
53:
Perfect timing. I'd love to see those 
skills in action.
57:
Sure! But only if you show me yours! 
Sounds like there are enough 
monsters for both of us!
71:
Is, is that Shining Eclair? 
What's she doing here?!
74:
I heard fighting! So I came to make 
this my stage for the day!
79: Get behind us—we'll take it from here!
92:
Thank you so much! Never in a million 
years would I have thought Eclair 
herself would come to our rescue!
94:
You did well holding off all those 
monsters. That was true courage!
100: All the world's a stage, huh?
103:
Hm? It's always like this when I come 
into town.
107: You seem like you're enjoying it.
111:
I am. Even if it makes for restless days 
off, the crowds bring me a kind of 
happiness.
112:
So long as my sword is sharp, the 
people are smiling, and life goes on... 
Well, I couldn't ask for much more, 
could I?—Except for a big dinner to top 
the day off!
116:
Hmm, so should we head for the 
tavern? Seems like a place with a lotta 
life.
120:
Good call. A table to write on WOULD 
make signing autographs easier!
123:
Autographs? That's not what I—
Just, just don't overdo it, okay?
126:
Never fear! My hand is drawn more to 
pub food than to pens.
130:
Come, everyone! Good cheer awaits 
us! Heck, I'll even sign the table itself—
Now where HAVEN'T I signed a table 
yet?
134:
If anyone knows a good place that'll fit 
this many people, please speak up!
